    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-15T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-15T05:00:00-05:00" n="495"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11634: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-15T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 15, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 15—6:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>American news correspondent from Nanking reports all Americans [and] other
                    foreigners in city uninjured except German named Sperling whose injury we
                    previously reported. Embassy employees safe and only damage to property suffered
                    by Counselor Peck’s<note n="43" xml:id="d495fn43">Willys R. Peck, Counselor of
                        Embassy in China, then at Hankow.</note> residence which was struck by
                    shrapnel.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Hankow, Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
